<TITLE> Blast in capital leaves 3 injured </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 5 (bdnews24.com)  A blast in front of a busy market the capital's Gulistan area left three injured on Thursday. Police could not immediately confirm the source of the explosion. The explosion occurred at around 2pm in front of Muktijoddha Market, Ramna zone deputy police commissioner Atiqul Islam told bdnews24.com. Thy injured were identified as Nasir Uddin, 45, a former Union Parishad chairman of Kochua in Bagerhat; Sheikh Nazrul Islam, 50, president of Bagerhat Bus Owners Association; Kartik Lal Das, 48, a passerby. Threy were taken to Dhaka Medical College Hospital, Islam said. Nasir Uddin condition was critical, he added. "We cannot say right now at the cause of the explosion," Islam told bdnews24.com at around 4pm. "We are investigating." Advocate Mir Shawkat Ali Badsah, a Bagerhat MP told bdnews24.com he went to the spot seeing a crowd gathering in front of the market on his way to Ramna Bhaban from the Secretariat. I saw three people, including two from my constituency, lying there bleding. "I took them to the hospital immediately," he said. Nazrul Islam and Nasir Uddin were local Awami League leaders in their area, the MP said. b
